  "heroImage": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/Panoramic_view_of_the_low-lying_landscape_of_Eastern_Island_2C_Midway_Atoll_-_2008.jpg",
  "headerNotes": [],
  "steps": [
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Identifying the islands",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_countrystreak.png",
              "imageLink": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_countrystreak.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The US Minor Outlying Islands are a chain of islands that are US overseas territories. As such, it is counted as **the US** for country streak purposes.",
              "The guide will be somewhat skewed towards the Midway Atoll, as that is the only island with pinpointable coverage.",
              "NOTE: The easiest way to locate the Midway Atoll on the map is to zoom in slightly to the west of the North Pacific Ocean map label."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_gen2.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/PJEEw73taHwJb65u7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The coverage on the Midway Atoll was made with a **Generation 2 camera**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_albatrosses.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/Kakx6BbTK2Mp61HV6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "One of the most distinct features of the Midway atoll is the presence of multiple **albatrosses** on almost every single location."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_runways.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/hpfryhPkGfAgZqjn6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "A large part of the coverage on the Midway Atoll was taken on two **runways**, which are the only areas where it can be difficult to spot the albatrosses."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_otherislands.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/YALv3V46aVBbjXds8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The islands other than the Midway Atoll can generally be characterised by three things. Firstly, the **Generation 3 trekker** coverage. Secondly, the low, **bushy** vegetation, and thirdly, the presence of numerous **birds**."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Region-specific clues",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_nicerunway.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/F9kQ53oULpwe9pna7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "A **nicely paved runway** can be seen going west to east on the southern side of the Midway Atoll."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_roughrunway.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/9LnkL81nBAfS9Qym8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "A **poorly paved runway** can be seen going north to south on the Midway Atoll. The pavement gets increasingly poor to the [north](https://goo.gl/maps/d45BgC8WQFuxeAE67)."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_town.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/hokkxYeomeYi5MPq7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "On the eastern side of the Midway Atoll, you can find a **small village**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_southeastisland.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/1z9K9Q9iAftdDTTz6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "Southeast Island is arguably the least distinctive island in the chain. It has a small lake near the centre, and a large amount of birds in the sky."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_lisianskiisland.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/F5psr4siuK3fiKR9A",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "Lisianski Island only has coverage right by the shore and can typically be recognised by the **large bushes** going around the entire island."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_laysanisland.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/cNLCGPvTvqv7LjXk8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "Laysan Island is the only island in the chain where the coverage has almost **no clouds**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_frenchairport.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/K6ZksuXBqhnuJbYs9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "The French Frigate Shoals is a fairly long and thin island with a shabby-looking runway. The island has by far the **largest number of birds** out of all islands in the chain."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_eastisland.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/oMVSWipvpK1mcT3U8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "East Island is the **smallest** island in the chain. There is barely any vegetation and you can see the ocean in all directions."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Spotlight",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_westcorner.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/i9mxerD8Z3eBzGQF7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "The western corner of the Midway Atoll runway is arguably the **most common location** on the official Geoguessr world map and may thus be worth remembering, particularly for a newer player."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/us-minor-outlying-islands/midway_tripods.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/gFcW5YXhgnCPArG6A",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "Eastern Island, situated right next to the Midway Atoll, has two small areas of low-quality **tripod coverage**. It does not have any other official coverage."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
